                <head>No. 290.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gibbs</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima, Peru</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-05-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 7, 1884</date>. (Received May 29.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 95.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The French minister, on 30th ultimo, passed a
                    note to Minister of Foreign Affairs that he had received a telegram authorizing
                    him to recognize the Iglesias Government immediately. It is also reported that
                    the Argentine Republic has recognized this Government. I suppose that all the
                    governments of any importance in Europe and the American continent have now
                    recognized this Government.</p>
                <p>Nothing of importance in political matters to communicate at present.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>RICHARD GIBBS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
